main event: On December 6, 1955, an unidentified object was observed over Marianna, Florida, climbing to 30,000 feet and then seen over Maxwell AFB, Alabama. The observation lasted approximately 5 minutes.
interesting points: The object was observed at a high altitude of 10 to 30,000 feet, displaying unusual climbing behavior.
The sighting involved potential radar confirmation of the object's altitude and trajectory.
The object was initially observed over Marianna, Florida and then proceeded to Montgomery, Alabama in just 5 minutes, indicating high speed.
Based on the available data, it was concluded that the object was a balloon, although there was insufficient data for evaluation.
The weather and winds at the time and location of the sighting were documented, adding meteorological context to the UFO report.
witnesses: Military personnel and air defense command
